    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="1" LastPage="15">
            <pdf>26201-jdecp-bosov.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>For a standard state stabilization problem of a linear stochastic differential system whose drift evolves in a direction determined by an independent Markov chain, a formulation with integer-valued constraints on the admissible control inputs is investigated. The stabilization objective is specified by a general quadratic functional. Cases with full information (the state of the chain is known) and with indirect observations (the system state serves as an indirect observation of the unknown chain state) are considered. In contrast to the solved unconstrained problem, the conditions for the existence of an optimal solution are not satisfied for the вЂњinteger-valuedвЂќ formulation. The task is to find and implement an Оµ-optimal control. It is shown that such a control is obtained by discretizing the optimal solution of the unconstrained problem and applying mixed-integer nonlinear programming. The implementation of Оµ-optimal control, due to the stochastic nature of the problem and the possibility of an unbounded number of switchings, may require excessive computational effort. A practically implementable approximation is obtained by a relaxation method: it is computed as the result of an integer-valued transformation of the optimal control in the unconstrained problem. Three variants of such transformations are proposed. A numerical experiment based on a model of the dynamic evolution of the position of a simple mechanical actuator is carried out. The computational results confirm the applicability of the proposed solutions with respect to the stabilization objective and also allow a comparison of relaxation strategies depending on the ''cost'' of the control input.</abstract>
            <title>Trajectory Stabilization of Linear Systems with Jump Drift Under Discrete Control Constraints</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>dynamic programming</word>
                <word>feedback control</word>
                <word>linear system stabilization</word>
                <word>mechanical drive</word>
                <word>mixed-integer nonlinear programming</word>
                <word>quadratic performance functional</word>
                <word>relaxation method</word>
                <word>Wonham filter</word>
            </keywords>
