    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="39" LastPage="62">
            <pdf>26204-jdecp-safonov.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>In this paper, S.A. Lomov's regularization method is generalized to nonlinear integro-differential equations with a zero operator
                of the differential part, with a rapidly varying kernel, and with a rapidly oscillating right-hand side. Such equations are regularized using the spectrum of the limit operator of the equivalent differential system. It is shown that nonlinearity plays a significant role in
                identifying essentially singularities in the solution of this problem. In the presence of only internal resonance between the eigenvalues ??of a rapidly oscillating inhomogeneity and the absence of external resonance with the spectral value of the integral operator, the essentially singular
                singularities are identified by the spectral value and spectrum of the oscillating inhomogeneity. An algorithm for constructing regularized (according to Lomov) asymptotic solutions is developed. The existence of such asymptotics is discussed, since in the presence of an arbitrary nonlinearity in the problem, such asymptotics may not exist, which is clearly demonstrated in the example given in the paper.</abstract>
            <title>Regularization and Asymptotic Solutions of a Nonlinear Integro-differential Equation with a Zero Operator of the Differential Part and a Rapidly Oscillating Inhomogeneity</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>regularization</word>
                <word>resonances</word>
                <word>singularly perturbed integro-differential equations</word>
                <word>solvability of iterative problems</word>
                <word>zero operator of the differential part</word>
            </keywords>
            <references>
                <reference>S. A. Lomov. Vvedeniye v obshchuyu teoriyu singulyarnykh vozmushcheniy [Introduction to the general theory of singular perturbations]. - M. : Nauka, 1981</reference>
                <reference>S. A. Lomov, I. S. Lomov. Osnovy matematicheskoy teorii pogranichnogo sloya [Fundamentals of the mathematical theory of the boundary layer]. - M. : Izd-vo Moskovskogo universiteta, 2011</reference>
                <reference>V. F. Safonov, A. A. Bobojanov. Kurs vysshey matematiki. Singulyarno vozmushchennyye zadachi i metod regulyarizatsii: uch. posobiye [Course of Higher Mathematics. Singularly Perturbed Problems and the Regularization Method: Tutorial]. - M. : Izdatel'skiy dom MEI, 2012</reference>
                <reference>V. F. Safonov, A. A. Bobojanov. Passage to the Limit in Singularly Perturbed Integro-Differential Equations with Zero Operator of the Differential Part//MPEI Bulletin. - 2006. - № 6. - P. 91-100. (In Russian)</reference>
                <reference>A. A. Bobodzhanov, B. T. Kalimbetov, V. F. Safonov. Metod regulyarizatsii dlya singulyarno vozmushchennykh zadach s bystro ostsilliruyushchimi koeffitsiyentami [Regularization method for singularly perturbed problems with rapidly oscillating coefficients]. - Shimkent, Elem, 2020</reference>
                <reference>M. A. Bobodzhanova. Singularly Perturbed Integro-Differential Systems with Zero Operator of the Differential Part// MPEI Bulletin. - 2010. - № 6. - P. 63-72. (In Russian)</reference>
